name: Biomimetic
description:
Frost Grape vines are entwined around a rusted hand-bound wire fence. The forms of the human made object designed to keep the wild at bay is aggressively enveloped by the same forms.

A fence such as this only serves as a psychological barrier to nature, nature will always find a way back to balance.

2016. Nikon D60, 55-200mm Lens.

Photographed in situ, without the use of artificial lighting or staging. Photoshop only used for resizing, and flipping.
